    "description": "Shutter is a short third-person puzzle game. You play as Keith, a new employee that has arrived at the mysterious research center L.I.E. (Learn, Investigate &amp; Exploit). Explore and make your way through to the last floor of the research center, jumping, climbing and using a mysterious camera that modifies objects using perspective.<br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2314110/extras/17688e487617350f6dabaa94dc6345ed.avif?t=1682697498\" width=640 height=360 /></span><br>Find different suits, collect documents and cassettes and find out what happened in this place. All in a space-age inspired setting.<br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2314110/extras/7236cff9ab148bb7a885bed8e3e93365.avif?t=1682697498\" width=640 height=360 /></span><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2314110/extras/fbd7818a03584b1659d1cfa64db0349f.avif?t=1682697498\" width=640 height=360 /></span><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >About the team</h2>Shutter is a graduation project made at ArtFx School of Digital Arts, with the collaboration of Audio Workshop and MAAAV Université Lumière Lyon 2.<br>Finalist for Best Student Game on the Bafta Student Awards, Independent Games Festival and The Rookies.",
